(22, '-beh, -be, -beh', 'suffix', 'intensifier (mild)', 'intensifier (mild)', '', '', 'often translatable as ''very'', or ''only'' (in the sense of ''exclusively''); occurs in word classes that -djahng and -bu occur on, and also occurs on responses and adverbs and on guram ''perhaps'' Gd; Crowley says of Wa that it only occurs on nouns and verbs, on nous usually ''only'', on verbs indicates completive aspect, often has little meaning; -be following a syllable with a long vowel. Holmer claims as shortened form of -bari ''having'', on yugambe/yugumbe ''having no'', and apparently in bariyahnbe (q.v.); however it is more probable that the older form was -bir (Watson).', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
