(55, '-dje', 'suffix', 'while, when', 'while ; when', '', '', 'on a verb indicates either a sequence or an overlapping of events in the future; if an event is thought as merely possible the simple indefinite form of the verb is used; if the event is considered quite probable, the repetitive -li is included; if the event is considered as being sure to happen, the definite morpheme may also be included.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
