(68, '-gah', 'suffix', 'associated with tree, suffix on tree names', 'tree name suffix', '', '', 'Calley in particular lists this suffix frequently, while some other sources often leave it off; sometimes specifies a tree rather than its products or another plant with similar features: gihmbi ''stinging nettle'', gihmbigah ''stinging tree'' (both sting), man.gur ''edible resin'', man.gurgah ''wattle tree'' (which exudes this resin) (Wa); occurs on many tree names in Gd and Wu and other dialects, eg bigin.gah, bigargah, waygargah, budjagah, bugimgah, buhyigan.gah, bulamgah.', '', '', 'Wa:Crowl; Wu:Calley ;', 'Gd:Geyt; Cop:Hargrv ga', '', '', '', '', ''),
