(117, '-li, -le', 'suffix', 'reflexive, antipassive', 'reflexive ; antipassive', '', '', 'basically a reflexive-reciprocal suffix in Wa; also ''antipassive'', ie the subject of a transitive verb with this suffix is not marked for ergative case (Wa, Gd); vowel /i/ changes to /e/ before an aspect suffix with vowel length (-hla, etc.); a variant -ri attested by Livingstone; see Grammar Notes', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
